It has since been updated a handful of times with the latest change happening
in 2012<sup>[15]</sup>. Notable changes include differentiation between initial
and final consonant sounds and a handful of vowel reworkings. The system was
also given an official name - "Rules of the Latin Alphabetical Transcriptions
of the Korean Language"<sup>[15]</sup>.

